Submerge Proposal Builder — Admin Pricing Manual
===============================================

Purpose
-------
This manual explains exactly how each input affects COGS and retail pricing in the current pricing engine.
It is written for admins who manage pricing models and need to explain “why this proposal costs what it costs.”

Core Pricing Pipeline (How everything rolls up)
-----------------------------------------------
1) The engine creates line items per category in `costBreakdown`.
2) Category totals are summed into `totals.grandTotal` (the raw COGS bucket before retail transforms).
3) Retail is computed from COGS using overhead + target margin + fixed/variable adjustments.

Retail math used by the app:
- `totalCostsBeforeOverhead = totals.grandTotal - customFeaturesAdjustmentTotal`
  - Note: negative custom-feature lines are treated as retail-only adjustments and are removed before COGS conversion.
- `totalCOGS = totalCostsBeforeOverhead * overheadMultiplier`
- `baseRetailPrice = ceil((totalCOGS / targetMargin) / 10) * 10`
- `retailPrice = baseRetailPrice + g3UpgradeCost + discountAmount + designerAdjustmentsTotal`
- `designerAdjustmentsTotal = manualAdjustmentsTotal + customFeaturesAdjustmentTotal + autoCoverRetailAdjustment`

Then the system computes:
- `digCommission = retailPrice * digCommissionRate`
- `adminFee = retailPrice * adminFeeRate`
- `closeoutCommission = retailPrice * closeoutCommissionRate`
- `grossProfit = retailPrice - totalCOGS - digCommission - adminFee - closeoutCommission`

Important defaults:
- overhead multiplier default: 1.01
- target margin default: 0.70
  - Admin field: `COGS vs Retail Price Increase` displays this as `70%`
- G3 fixed retail adder: 1,250

Category-by-Category Cost Logic (COGS)
--------------------------------------

A) Plans & Engineering
- Added only when a pool definition exists.
- Line items:
  - Pool Only (always, qty 1)
  - Spa (if spa exists)
  - Waterfall (explicit waterfall count or waterfall feature-derived count)
  - Water Features (count of non-waterfall selected features)
  - Soil Sample / Engineer (if excavation flag set)

B) Layout
- Added only when a pool definition exists.
- Line items:
  - Pool Only (always, qty 1)
  - Spa (if spa exists)
  - Silt Fencing (if selected)

C) Permit
- Added only when a pool definition exists.
- Line items:
  - Pool Only (always, qty 1)
  - Spa (if spa exists)
  - Permit Runner (always, qty 1)

D) Excavation
- Main drivers:
  - Base excavation by area range (gunite)
  - Over 1,000 sqft overage
  - Additional 6" depth adders above 8'
  - RBB by each entered level length/height
  - Gunite spa base + raised spa adders
  - Site prep hours
  - Backfill (gunite)
  - Gravel install by pool area
  - Fiberglass install/gravel (fiberglass pool path)
  - Dirt haul (computed from overdig area/depth + spa allowance)
  - Auto-cover box by pool width
  - Travel
  - Misc (gunite)

E) Plumbing
- Added only when a pool definition exists.
- Line items can include:
  - Short Stub (always)
  - Spa Base (gunite spa)
  - Pool Overrun / Spa Overrun (when runs exceed thresholds)
  - 2.0" pipe, 2.5" pipe, 3.0" pipe (from run formulas)
  - Water Feature run setup + overage lines
  - Additional Water Feature Run line
  - In-floor plumbing
  - Conduit (uses electrical run + light run * conduit multiplier)
  - Manifold (always)
  - Strip Forms (always)
  - Cleaner line
  - Auto-fill line
  - Additional skimmers
  - Valve Actuator in Misc. Plumbing
- Valve Actuator quantity = number of unique selected water-feature zones/subcategories.
  - Example: Wok Pot + Bubbler = 2 actuators.
  - Example: quantity 2 of Bubblers only = 1 actuator.

F) Gas
- Only appears when `plumbing.runs.gasRun > 0`.
- Line items:
  - Base Gas Set
  - Gas Overrun (above threshold)

G) Steel (gunite only)
- Skipped entirely for fiberglass pools.
- Line items:
  - Pool Base (perimeter-based)
  - 4-Bar Beam
  - Spa Base (gunite spa)
  - Raised Spa + Spa Double Curtain (raised gunite spa)
  - Steps & Bench
  - Tanning Shelf
  - Additional 6" depth
  - RBB Steel by entered RBB levels
  - Double Curtain
  - Pool Bonding
  - Muck Out
  - Travel

H) Electrical
- Added only when a pool definition exists.
- Line items:
  - Base Electrical (includes first run allowance)
  - Homerun overrun above threshold
  - Lights (additional lights beyond first)
  - Heater electrical (if a valid heater is selected)
  - Automation
  - Bonding
  - Outlet
  - Heat Pump Electrical base + overrun

I) Shotcrete (Labor + Material)
- Gunite only (skipped for fiberglass).
- Yardage is computed from perimeter, interior area, RBB, spa, bullnose, double curtain, raised spa, etc.
- Labor lines can include:
  - Minimum Labor
  - Add'l Labor over minimum yard threshold
  - Spa
  - Auto Cover
  - Distance adders
  - Travel
- Material lines can include:
  - Pool Material per yard
  - Auto Cover material
  - Clean Out
  - Env/Fuel per yard
  - Miscellaneous
  - Travel
  - Tax lines (county-sensitive: MECK split, NC state-only, default combined)

J) Tile / Coping / Decking / Rockwork
1. Tile
- Tile labor = perimeter + additional tile length
- Spa tile labor when spa perimeter exists
- Optional step-trim tile
- Material includes Level 1 base and Level 2/3 upgrades

2. Coping
- Coping length uses entered value OR derived default formula
- Labor = copingRate(copingType) * copingLength
- Material = copingMaterialRate(copingType) * materialQty
- Flagstone uses quantity multiplier
- 16x16 coping adds 33% labor and 33% material surcharges as separate lines

3. Decking
- Non-concrete decking uses area with waste factor
- Concrete path uses concrete-band/base/additional calculations with ceiling behavior
- Concrete labor has special cantilever condition
- Concrete steps labor/material are separate
- Concrete pump is a separate fixed line when concrete work exists
- Fiberglass pools can add a concrete band material line

4. Bullnose / Spillway / Rockwork
- Bullnose labor + material by linear feet
- Spillway labor + material
- Rockwork (panel ledge/stacked stone/tile) uses labor/material with waste factors

5. Material tax split
- Engine separates tile material, coping/deck material, and rockwork material,
  then applies tax lines per subtotal bucket.

K) Drainage
- For each drain type (downspout, deck, french, box):
  - total = baseCost + max(0, LF - includedFt) * perFtOver

L) Equipment Ordered
- Includes Base White Goods + selected equipment/addons.
- Typical lines:
  - Pump
  - Auxiliary pump(s)
  - Filter
  - Cleaner
  - Heater
  - VersaFlo upgrade delta
  - Pool/Spa lights (grouped by selected light)
  - Automation + Additional Zones
  - Salt system
  - Auto-fill system
  - Accessories (blanket reel, solar blanket, fallback auto-fill, handrail, startup chemicals)
  - Equipment Tax (separate line on equipment subtotal)

M) Equipment Set (separate category)
- Base Equipment Set
- Heater set (heater vs heat-pump set pricing)
- Pool Bonding
- Additional Pump set charge per auxiliary pump count

N) Water Features
- Each selected feature maps to catalog COGS and quantity.
- Water feature COGS formula:
  - `featureCOGS = basePrice + addCost1 + addCost2`
- In master rollup, selected water-feature items are remapped into Equipment before equipment-tax rebuild.
- Water-feature custom options remain in the Water Features category.

O) Interior Finish + Water Truck
- Gunite only (skipped for fiberglass).
- Interior area computed from pool geometry; minimum charge sqft enforced.
- Lines can include:
  - Base finish
  - Spa finish
  - Pool prep base + over-threshold prep
  - Spa prep threshold line
  - Misc
  - Travel
  - Step & bench detail over threshold
  - Waterproofing / Microglass (+ raised spa variant)
  - Fittings line (drains/vac/returns/hydro)
  - Water Truck loads based on total gallons and load-size capacity

P) Cleanup
- Base Pool Cleanup
- Spa Cleanup
- Over 500 sqft
- RBB Cleanup
- Travel
- Rough Grading

Q) Fiberglass Shell + Fiberglass Install
1. Fiberglass Shell
- Pool shell (from model price or size price)
- Spa shell
- Spillover
- Shell discount line (configured discount rate)
- Shell tax line

2. Fiberglass Install
- Freight by size
- Optional surcharge
- Crane options (pool + spa)
- Install labor by size/spa
- Gravel by size
- Water by size

R) Masonry / Stone
- Columns (when facing selected)
- RBB facing
- Raised spa facing (with waste factors)
- Raised spa spillway labor/material
- Retaining walls (configured wall type/height cost model)
- Master engine may add an extra rockwork material tax line for masonry subtotal.

S) Custom Options and Custom Features
- Most sections support “custom options” where line total is:
  - `laborCost + materialCost`
- Custom Features section uses:
  - explicit labor+material when present, else fallback `totalCost`
- Automatic Cover manufacturer cost is inserted as a Custom Features COGS line when enabled and priced.

T) PAP Discounts
- PAP discounts are applied as negative line items in target categories.
- Equipment PAP discount is inserted before tax, and equipment tax is recalculated on discounted base.
- Tile/Coping material PAP discount has special flagstone-target behavior.

Detailed Examples
-----------------

Example 1 — Pump selected (Equipment)
- COGS unit cost comes from `getEquipmentItemCost`:
  - If partized fields exist: `basePrice + addCost1 + addCost2`
  - If `percentIncrease` exists, that partized sum is transformed by the configured divisor logic
  - Else fallback to `price`
  - Then for pumps, multiply by `pumpOverheadMultiplier`
- Equipment line total:
  - `pumpLineTotal = pumpUnitCost * quantity`
- Equipment tax line then applies on equipment subtotal.
- That subtotal flows to `equipmentOrdered`, then to `grandTotal`, then into COGS->retail transforms.

Example 2 — Coping = Travertine Level 1
- Coping labor:
  - `labor = copingRate(travertine-level1) * copingLength`
- Coping material:
  - `material = copingMaterialRate(travertine-level1) * copingMaterialQty`
- If coping size = 16x16:
  - Add `+33%` coping labor surcharge and `+33%` coping material surcharge as separate line items.
- If spillway/bullnose/rockwork are selected, they add separate lines.
- Material taxes are added after subtotals by material bucket.

Admin Checklist (what to verify when totals look wrong)
--------------------------------------------------------
1) Confirm proposal has valid pool definition (many categories short-circuit without it).
2) Confirm correct pricing model/franchise context is active.
3) Verify critical geometry fields: perimeter, surface area, depths, spa settings.
4) Verify run lengths: plumbing/electrical/gas/heat-pump.
5) Verify all boolean toggles: raised spa, auto cover, silt fence, rough grading, etc.
6) Check custom options/features for unintended negative values.
7) Check PAP discount percentages.
8) Check manual adjustment values.
9) Check county (shotcrete material tax behavior differs).
10) Re-open cost breakdown and inspect which line item is driving the change.

Notes on Pricing Data and Overrides
-----------------------------------
- All rates are sourced from pricing data tied to the active franchise/model.
- The formulas in code are stable; admins typically change only the rate tables.
- When rates are changed in Admin Pricing, all future calculations use the updated values.
